    answer: "RRF solves the score-incompatibility problem: BM25 scores are unbounded positive numbers; cosine similarity is [-1, 1]. Naïve weighted average = meaningless.\n\nRRF throws away scores and operates on RANKS only:\n  score(d) = Σ weight_i / (k + rank_i(d))\n\nk=60 default: dampens extreme rank differences. Without k, rank 1=1.0, rank 2=0.5 (extreme cliff). With k=60, rank 1=0.0164, rank 10=0.0143 — gentler slope.\n\nDocument at rank 3 (BM25) + rank 7 (dense):\n  = 1/(60+3) + 1/(60+7) = 0.01587 + 0.01493 = 0.0308\n\nDocument at rank 1 in both: highest possible score.\n\nTune k: large corpus → k=60. Small corpus (<300 docs) → k=10-20 for steeper rank differentiation.",
